<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="19" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="19">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="19">
This species is widely distributed from Brazil to northeast Argentina (
<bibRefCitation author="Chagas-Jr, A" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="18" pageNumber="31" pagination="57 - 67" refId="B20" refString="Chagas-Jr, A, Knysak, I, Guizze, SPG, 2007. Revalidation of the subgenus Dactylotergitius Verhoeff, and redescription of Otostigmus (D.) caudatus Broelemann and Otostigmus (D.) cavalcantii Bucherl (Scolopendromorpha: Scolopendridae: Otostigminae). Zootaxa 1639: 57 - 67" title="Revalidation of the subgenus Dactylotergitius Verhoeff, and redescription of Otostigmus (D.) caudatus Broelemann and Otostigmus (D.) cavalcantii Bucherl (Scolopendromorpha: Scolopendridae: Otostigminae)." volume="1639" year="2007">Chagas-Jr et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
). Though more common in southeast Brazil, it has also been found in the central, northeastern, and northern regions. Our records place the species in sandstone caves from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pará">Para</normalizedToken>
and in one limestone cave from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
Paulo. Accidental in caves.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="19" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="19">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="19">Cave (under rocks).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="19" type="conservation">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="19">Conservation.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="19">
Even with these few records, the wide distribution suggests that this species is not under threat. However, their range in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pará">Para</normalizedToken>
is located within the boundaries of a large hydroelectrical dam (Belo Monte) (M.E. Bichuette, per. obs.), suggesting the possibility of a local threat.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
